HEADWORD: Culinary
<hw>Cu"li*na*ry</hw> <pr>(k?"l?-n?-r?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>culinarius</ets>, fr. <ets>culina</ets> kitchen, perh. akin to
<ets>carbo</ets> coal: cf. F. <ets>culinare</ets>.]</ety> <def>Relating
to the kitchen, or to the art of cookery; used in kitchens; <as>as, a
<ex>culinary</ex> vessel; the <ex>culinary</ex> art</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

